review_blob: Nice amber color with white vanishing head. Strong taste of malt and alcohol, which is also found in the taste. The balance in the beer is too much towards alcohol to really hit my taste.
Amber in color with a medium head. Aroma is strong and sweet with a lot of malt. The taste is rich and sweet with an ok balance between malt and sweetness.

Dark orange in color with a quickly vanishing head. The aroma is strong, malty and sweet. The taste is overwhelming - I thought I had opened a Brune, but this is more like a barley wine! The taste is dominated by (too much) sweetness, malt and some citrus notes. The palate is rich. Overall an interesting beer with a balance I do not fancy.

Very dark in color with a large brownish and lasting head. The aroma is dominated by a lightly roasted malt. The roasted malt is found again in the taste with a well balanced sweetness a a rich creamy palette. A rather good double!

Pours a nice dark amber color with medium lasting light brown head. The aroma is rather fresh and light considering it is a dubbel. The taste is rather disappointing, with a thin palate and heavy on carbonate giving a acid touch to the aftertaste. Definitely there are much better dubbels out there

Umm a sonny evening in the garden accomplished by a red Chimay, not too bad. The color is hazy amber with a rather large light brownish head. The form is kind a large bobbled so it vanished in a few minutes. The aroma is sweet malty and the taste fills the mouth with distinct malt.
Hazy yellow color with medium lasting white head. Distinct strong aroma with hobs and alcohol. The taste is strong and full bodied but reminds me fare more of a triple than the IPAs that I fancy.
Well a nice blond good for a sunny hot evening. Yellow color with white head. Fresh aroma and a rather rich body.
Orange color with white lasting head. Fruity aroma. The taste has some bitterness but it could easily have taken more.

Brown/red color with a nice medium lasting head.Aroma with alcohol, a little malt and sweetness. The feeling in the mouth is rich with a distinct taste of roasted malt a little bitterness and again some sweetness. A rather special but well composed beer.
Hmm rather good in this hot spring afternoon... Color is orange with white head. Aroma is sweet, and so is the taste. Not very complex, but rather refreshing.

To be honest; this is really not my type of beer. If it in rare cases needs to be a stout then be it, but to combine with added sugar (chocolate) no way. Well - aroma is sweet and a little roasted. The roasted taste is well in the mouse as well, but the overwhelming sweetness of the chocolate, combined with the low level of carbonation is really bizzare. In addition the palate could in my opinion have been more rich.
Yellow color with small fast vanishing head. The aroma is rather fruity with a touch of malt. The taste is fresh and medium hoppy and to the sweet side. For a lager this is one of the better...
Orange color with large creamy lasting head. Hobby and fruity aroma. When it comes to the taste however the bitterness is a bit to the week side disappointing a bit and just too little carbonate too.
Golden orange color with medium size and lasting head. The aroma is fresh with notes of malt and a little citrus. The taste is rather sharp and unbalanced - not really one of my favorites.
Dark red amber color with medium creamy off white head. The aroma is fruity and to the sweet side. The taste is rather rich with rather lot of malt and a rich palate.
Yellow color with a huge white long lasting head. The aroma is strong with a little fruit. The taste is marked with alcohol combined with a little more sweetness than typical in a triple.

Well, well I would have expected a more heavy impression from this Stout. The color is true black with a little brown lasting head. The aroma is light with roasted notes. The roasted tasted notes are also found in the flavor, however the palette is disappointing thin for such a beer.

Orange color with very quick vanishing head. The aroma is a little heavy sweet to the caramel side. The taste is very very sweet with a strong influence of alcohol. Not the best doppelbock in my opinion.
Brown color with light white head. Powerful roasted aroma with light fruitiness. The taste is dominated by roasted malt with a hint of hobs.

Hazy amber color with medium size light brown head. The aroma is not particular strong, but what is reveals some of the hobs. The beer has a rather powerful palate which stimulates the most of your mouth. The taste is obviously dominated by bitterness from the hobs, even though it is not that pronounced as one could expect. In overall just above average IPA.
A nice beer! Amber color with moderate head. Malty aroma with a lot of sweetness and some hobs. The texture in the mouth is reach, creamy with a nice balanced taste between malt, hobs and sweetness.

Bought this can of beer for DKK 5,- in the local discount super market. This is really value for money considering the alternative to this being industrial pilsners or lagers. The color is orange / light amber with quick vanishing white head. The aroma is fruity and fresh. The taste is light (actually too light to my taste) and fresh with fruit notes and a rather thin palette.
2008 edition. Hazy brown color with small off white head. The aroma is dominated with sweet caramel. The taste is thin of a Christmas beer. Light spicy with sweetness.

Umm I like this. Amber color with large light brown head. The aroma i heavy with citrus and a faint touch of nuts. The taste is dominated with cascade and chinook adding to the citrus and giving a long lasting heavy taste.
Dark cloudy with brown head. Malty aroma. The taste is malty with a little sweetness and a nice rich creamy palate.

2008 edition! Dark reddish color with brown long lasting head. Aroma is sweet and malty. Enters the mouth with a rather rich palette but leaves a somehow messy picture dominated by anise. Actually I like the beer even as it is not splendid.
Very light yellow color with nice long lasting white head. The aroma is weak malty. The taste is light with a little yeast and faint malt.
Amber color with light brown quick vanishing head. The aroma is distinct with sweetness and some undefined spiciness. The flavor is dominated by sweetness which is somehow synthetic close to orange.
Umm I like this one. The color is hazy dark amber with high long lasting brown head. Sweet strong aroma. The taste is rich with a dominating sweetness and some spicy background.
Amber color with little light brown head. The aroma is citrus like and fresh. Bitter rich taste very well balanced. I like this one.
Tasted as Brglum Kloster  - Bispens Trippel. Hazy yellow with small white head. Light fruity aroma. Taste is typical trippel with fruity aroma with strong alcohol notes.

Dark color with reddish glow. Small fast vanishing head. The first sniff definitely promise something different. The aroma is full and smokey, and reminds you of one of those strong whiskeys. Obviously the smokey notes also dominate the taste with the slight bitterness from the oak cask. A bit disappointing is the rather thin palate.
Dark amber color with medium head. The aroma is strong and sweet malty. A full rich taste, a bit to the sweet side.

This was on tap at Carina and Henriks wedding so I had plenty of it!! From what I remember it comes out very dark with a medium size brown head. The taste is rich, but the finer details are unfortunately lost in a fainting memory.
Amber color with small to medium white head. Intense malthy aroma. Rich flavour of malt with a roasted touch and just a little sweetness.
Hazy yellow color with nice white head. Aroma is week with just a touch of fruit. The taste is fresh and mild but not very pronounced.
Dark brown with light brown long lasting head. Sweet malty aroma. Rounded taste with malt and a little sweetness. A quite good dunkel.
Black with brown creamy head. Roasted aroma with fruit notes. Full body taste with roasted sweetness.
Amber color with medium creamy head. Roasted aroma. The taste is roasted (towards swartsbeer) with (too) much sweetness.

Golden color with long lasting medium size white head. Spicy aroma with hob notes. The beer fills your mouth with a well balanced flavour of citrus hobs and a bitter aftertaste, but absolutely to the mild side of an IPA.
beer_name: Carlsberg Semper Ardens First Gold I.P.A.

review_blob: Amber color with big creamy long standing head. Sweet taste with roasted notes. I like this one.

You take a bad beer and make it worse... What is this for, I cant believe that there is a market for this - well anyway: Yellow color with quick vanishing white head. Sharp aroma with hints of malt. Very thin palate (thinner than a normal Tuborg pilsner if possible). The taste is thin - I mean really thin like water with a faint touch of malt.
Orange color with full size white head. The aroma is light malty so is the flavor. Aftertaste is quickly vanishing. A slight disappointment.

This is heavy stuff! Brown reddish color with long standing off white head. Aroma is slight sour with a full sweetness. The feeling in the mouth is heavy very sweet with notes of caramel and quite a lot of alcohol.

Orange color with very big creamy white head. The aroma is fresh and fruity. The brew is slight bitter with a note of pepper in the end. he fruit is still there but less pronounced in the flavor than in the aroma. I like this beer for its freshness.

Brown color with very quick vanishing head. Aroma have notes of yeast and fruit. When the beer enters the mouth it is an easy drinkable one with a well balanced taste of light roasted malt, prickling fruit and a thin slice of yeast. A good light beer but other Trappistes have more to offer.

Orange color with quick vanishing light brown head. Weak aroma with a little carbonate. The taste is like an average industry product not very inspiring and only only slight notes of slightly roasted malts and carbonate.

Dark brown to black color with thin ivory head. Aroma of roasted malt. The taste is dominated with roasted malt nearly smokey and not many other tones are coming through. A quite good representative of a Schwarzbier.
Dark brown with small light brown head. Roasted aroma so is the flavor. A little anomenous brew.
